One of the most widely adopted open-standard languages for modelling dynamical systems is Modelica ( http://www.modelica.org ), a general-purpose fully-ﬂedged language based on ordinary differential as well as algebraic equations plus procedural snippets.

A Modelica model can also be easily exported into a Functional Mock- Up Unit (FMU), an executable opaque (binary) object implementing the Functional Mock-Up Interface (FMI, http://fmi-standard.org ), one of the currently most widespread open standards for model exchange, integration and co-simulation.
